Video call and chat options
Audio and video calls to others who are using MS Teams are available using the MS Teams Call app. 

Webex does not have Instant Messaging (IM) or chat room services.  If you have a Jabber chat room you can still use Jabber, but it is highly recommended that you migrate it into a MS Teams channel as soon as possible.

Step 1: Install the Webex app
Cisco Call requires you to download and install Webex. Webex is available for downloading on the respective platform sites:

UB-issued machines:
Windows - Software Center
Mac - Self Service app
Self-managed machines - https://www.webex.com/downloads.html
iPhone - App Store
Android - Google play
Search on Webex and follow the installation instructions.  For mobile devices, make sure to install the Webex client and not the Webex Meeting app.

During installation allow all the access it requests or else it will not run properly.

Once installed, the Webex Calling client will run silently in the background.

Step 2: Add Cisco Call to Teams and pin to the App Bar
1. At the bottom of the left panel (“App Bar”), click on the +Apps button

2. Enter Cisco Call in the search bar

3. Select Open

Zoom image: Click Open after you search for Cisco Call.Click Open after you search for Cisco Call.
4. Cisco Call will now appear at the bottom of the App Bar.  Right-click and Pin it or else it will disappear from the App Bar:

Zoom image: Pin Cisco Call to your App Bar in TeamsPin Cisco Call to your App Bar in Teams.
E911 Settings on a PC or Mac
Manually-created entries for locations take precedence over discovered locations
Location instructions:

On Campus using a wired connection: NO ACTION REQUIRED.
On Campus using a wireless connection or working remotely: DO NOT SET YOUR LOCATION AHEAD OF TIME.  Manually set your location using the steps below when physically present at that location.
Wired connections on campus
Do not set anything in relation to e911.  The 9line e911 system will automatically discover your device and determine your work location to the UB building and specific room for all UB documented wired network connections.

Adding campus locations (when connected using Wi-Fi)
Manually set your location using the steps below when physically present at that location.

1. When setting the first location, for Windows go to Hidden Icons in the taskbar and open the Webex app. For Mac, open the Webex app from your Applications

Zoom image: Click the caret in the task bar and select the Webex appClick the caret in the task bar and select the Webex app.
2. Click E911 settings

Zoom image: select e911 settingsselect e911 settings.
3. Add a label such as Work. You must use the Official UB Building Service address as base address and add specific room location in the available free-form field at the bottom:

North Campus – Amherst, NY 14260
South Campus – Buffalo, NY 14214
Downtown Campus – Buffalo, NY 1420X
Zoom image: enter a dispatchable address, including UB zip codeenter a dispatchable address, including UB zip code.
4. After selecting Save, the client will confirm that you set a dispatchable location. 

When done correctly you will see Address successfully saved
Zoom image: Address successfully saved will appearAddress successfully saved will appear.
If it doesn’t find a match with a valid address, you will have to try again
Zoom image: If the address is invalid, you will see an error message that the address entered is invalid.If the address is invalid, you will see an error message that the address entered is invalid.
Adding a home office (work from home) location
For your alternate work location (work from home), manually create and set that work location when physically present (this only needs to be done once).
Your official address for a home office is your official home mailing address. 
When entering a home office location, everything must be a 100% match with what’s on file with your local county or else the address lookup with fail with “Address not found”.  That is, if you enter “Maple Road” it will fail because it is registered as “Maple Rd”.

If you’re uncertain of the syntax, use Google Maps to get the correct information for your location.

Open Webex:
For Windows, go to Hidden Icons (^) in the taskbar and open the Webex app
For Mac, open the Webex app from your Applications
Select E911 settings
Click Clear address 
Enter a label such as Home and then enter your home address as it is recorded with the county
Click Save: 
If it is successful, you are set
If it is not successful, change the information (e.g., Rd instead of Road) until the address saves successfully
Smartphones and 911 calls
When on your smartphone, Webex will automatically send 911 calls out the native dialer and use your cellular provider’s tracking for a location. Do not set a location manually.

Audio Settings
Check the Webex/Cisco Call Audio Settings to confirm your preferred devices are selected.  These are independent of the settings in MS Teams and may not necessarily match.

1. In MS Teams click on Call settings

Zoom image: Click Call SettingsClick Call Settings.
2. Click Audio in the pop-up and make adjustments to select your desired device and volume, and the correct microphone:

In Webex the default Ringers and Alerts setting is All Devices and is set at a loud volume.  Use the pulldown to select the preferred device and/or adjust the volume control.
Check that the correct microphone is being used to avoid poor call quality at the far end of the conversation.
Zoom image: Select Audio and adjust settings as desired.Select Audio and adjust settings as desired.
